    "summary": "In his 21 years in practice, Floris Pierik has advised on M&A transactions with an aggregate value in excess of \u20ac90 billion. He advises public and private national and international groups, private equity clients, and other financial sponsors on domestic and cross-border transactions. Complex M&A and private equity transactions and investments for corporates and financial sponsors are central to his work. Some of his major deals include targets with operations on a European or global scale, often with a significant U.S. connection.\n \nFloris advises on transactions in a variety of industries including technology, chemicals and manufacturing.\n \nFloris's key transactions at Jones Day include advising Nasdaq-listed BioMarin Pharmaceutical on the \u20ac680 million public takeover offer for Prosensa Holding NV; Gimv, Draper Esprit, and Robert Bosch Ventures on the sale of Greenpeak Technologies to Nasdaq-listed Qorvo; Randstad on the public takeover offer for Monster; NYSE-listed The Timken Company as successful bidder in the $280 million controlled auction sale of Groeneveld Group; Gimv on multiple mandates including the investments in UDB, Joolz, Snack Connection, and Coolworld Rentals; Aurelius Equity Opportunities on the \u20ac220 million controlled auction sale of Getronics Group, the \u20ac330 million controlled auction sale of Solidus Group to funds managed by Centrebridge Partners and the sale of Office Depot Europe to RAJA SA; Arsenal Capital Partners on the controlled auction sale of IGM Resins group to Astorg; SUEZ on the sale of its recycling and recovery operations in The Netherlands, Germany, Luxembourg, and Poland to Pre-Zero; Groupe Solmax on the acquisition of TenCate Geosynthetics; and Fortino Capital, Ventech,  HenQ and founders on the sale of inSided to Gainsight Inc.\n \nPrior to joining Jones Day, Floris was a counsel at a leading international law firm, where he worked on high-profile public and private M&A and private equity transactions\n",
